underlying_goal: The user wanted to understand and fix a discrepancy between the script's console output and the generated report file.
primary_success: Claude correctly identified the root cause of the bug: two different functions in two different files were generating the same report filename with slightly different logic, leading to a mismatch.
brief_summary: A user was confused when their script reported 10 selected prompts, but the report file they viewed only contained 2. Claude investigated and found a bug where two different parts of the code were generating the report filename with inconsistent logic. Claude fixed the bug to use a single source of truth for the path and archived the old, confusingly-named files.
